The ever helpful and peppy evil witch, casually carrying around the reliquary in which she so villainously restrained the poor princess, would hear the request of her captive. Like any self respecting malicious person, she'd immediately stop to follow her request.

Putting down the palanquin very gently onto the ground, with attentive care Lupe would respond;

"Okay, sure!" She nodded and grinned, she was familiar with enough Alecto where she didn't speak in shouting villainous lines perpetually. She would walk over to the tree and  start analysing which would be the best.

She pouted, turned her gaze downward to avert from looking directly into Alecto's own;

"M-my pa- My mark of the *beast*... It's not for everyone you know! I don't put it on everything! Okay?"  She gulped

"But we can go bully the metal man, like cover him in mean and evil flower shapes!"

"But I want to win them for you." She seemed confused. "I don't care about prizes."

Looking down in deep thought the witch would simply shrug after coming to a conclusion;

"I guess I just have to win them all."

As red portals appeared like zits all over the surface of the town radiating tainted mana Lupe would stare befuddled for a brief second at the carnage they caused. They were enemies, it was easy enough to understand. 

"Princess! We got to go!" She yelped urgently, putting the palanquin down she'd pull back the veil and extend her arms out; 

"We need to leave your prison behind for now." The witch said, with a sincere look of apology in her eyes.
